1604379600.title: Bargain Hunt
1604379600.descr: Anita Manning travels by steam to the Elsecar Heritage Centre in Yorkshire. She is joined by experts Kate Bliss and Jonathan Pratt, who help the reds and blues bag a bargain that will hopefully make a profit at the auction with Knutsford auctioneer Nick Hall. Anita also pays a visit to Stockport's Hat Works Museum to find out about the town's hatting heyday.

1604382300.title: Bargain Hunt
1604382300.descr: Two teams of amateur antique collectors meet at an antiques fair to compete to make the largest profit from a three hundred pound budget. Once the contestants have done the shopping for their own items, the experts then take any leftover money and go shopping for more antiques which is 'bonus buys'. The teams then have to decide whether or not to take these items to auction.

1604385000.title: Father Brown
1604385000.descr: Father Brown is a Catholic priest and an amateur detective solving murder cases, set during the 1950s in the fictional village Kembleford in Cotswold area, England. He uses his own wits as well as skills of his close friends, and being a priest allows him to look straight to the truth. He is strongly against the capital punishment for the capital crimes, as still applied in Britain of that time.

1604388000.title: Atlantis
1604388000.descr: One day Jason wakes up on an island where there are demigods and other mythological creatures. He meets Hercules and learns that he is in Atlantis. The two are joined by the highly intelligent Pythagoras. The three of them roam the countryside and meet creatures like Medusa or the Furies. Not infrequently, the three adventurers must defend themselves against evil forces.

1604390700.title: Impossible
1604390700.descr: Entertaining and educational British quiz show, hosted by Rick Edwards, where 24 regular contestants compete throughout the series to answer tricky questions. But some of the optional answers are designed to be ''impossible'', or at the very least inconsistent with the information given. The participants must avoid selecting these booby trap answer and the best one wins the £10,000 jackpot.

1604433600.title: Scott & Bailey
1604433600.descr: Follow personal and professional lives of Detectives Janet Scott and Rachel Bailey, members of the Major Incident Team- MIT, within the fictional Manchester Metropolitan Police who solve difficult cases and fight crime whilst risking their lives on a daily basis in order to help those in need.

1604436300.title: Rillington Place
1604436300.descr: The shocking true story of the serial killer John Christie is retold in this compelling three-part drama series. Directed by Craig Viveiros, the series chronicles the life of Christie, beginning with the break out of WWII and up to his execution, revealing the toxic marriage with his wife Ethel and the relationship he had with neighbour Timothy Evans. Featuring performances from Tim Roth, Nico Mirallegro, Samantha Morton, Jodie Comer and Eiry Thomas.

1604439600.title: Friday Night Dinner
1604439600.descr: A family comedy about a Jewish family who meet for dinner every Friday night. The family includes mother Jackie, father Martin, and two sons Adam (Simon Bird) and Jonathan. The episodes consist of disruptions to the dinner by Adam and Jonathan arguing or by neighbor Jim Bell (Mark Heap.) It began just a year after the show The Inbetweeners finished, and worked as a new series for fans to watch.

1604441100.title: New Tricks
1604441100.descr: Popular long-running BBC crime drama about the trials and tribulations of aging officers as they attempt to solve the cold cases of yesteryear while coming to terms with their own years. Over the course of its 12 seasons it charted the work of the Metropolitan Police fictional unsolved crimes department, drawing its title from the adage of not being able to teach old dogs new tricks.
